Not sure if it is of any use, but I faced potentially related problem with `Get-PhysicalDisk` in 7.2.5 (have not tried other versions) called from a desktop C# app via SDK, where it would seemingly randomly return empty collection without any errors within the same program run. If anyone is interested in looking into it, I can try capturing a memory dump when that happens.

My setup is
```csharp
Runspace.DefaultRunspace = RunspaceFactory.CreateRunspace();
Runspace.DefaultRunspace.Open();

using var ps = PowerShell.Create(RunspaceMode.CurrentRunspace);
ps.AddCommand("Set-ExecutionPolicy")
    .AddParameter("ExecutionPolicy", "RemoteSigned")
    .AddParameter("Scope", "Process")
    .Invoke();
```
the first thing upon program startup (literally the first lines of `Main`)

Then I a launch a separate `Background==true` thread for all `Get-PhysicalDisk` calls that boils down to this:

```csharp
var runspace = RunspaceFactory.CreateRunspace();
runspace.Name = "Runspace-Get-PhysicalDisk";
runspace.Open();

Runspace.DefaultRunspace = runspace;

while (true) {
   WaitForRequestToRunGetPhysicalDisk();

    using var ps = PowerShell.Create();
    ps.AddCommand("Get-PhysicalDisk");
    var results = ps.Invoke();
    if (ps.HadErrors) throw new Exception(ps.Streams.Error);
    Debug.Assert(results.Count > 0); // this assert fails now and then

  SendResultToRequester(results);
}
```
